			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Shadowfrost wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>No, that wouldn't be acceptable at all.&nbsp; A druid can buff her group with no reagent cost for less than 2k mana.&nbsp; Why should I spend 6k mana to achieve the same thing?</BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Not that I would any way mind not having to tote around a pack fulla dots....</P>
<P>How can you compare a druid's buffs to ours?</P>
<P>Druid: Soe, prot 9, dam shield, strength, regen.&nbsp; That's about it.&nbsp;&nbsp; So really we're only talking about prot 9 - 618hps 32ac.</P>
<P>Cleric: Faith 520hp 22 ac, Ward of Gallantry 54 ac,&nbsp; Symbol of Kazad 910hps.</P>
<P>Faith + wog &gt; 9 and costs no components.&nbsp;&nbsp; Kazad is an EXTRA that clerics get for those situations where someone really needs the extra hps, and we pay for it.&nbsp;&nbsp; The fact that everyone and their dog is now so used to running around with Virtue purchased in PoK and whatnot has nothing to do with it's intended role in the game.</P>
<P>Im not arguing that we should have to pay for components.&nbsp; Im arguing that there is valid reason to charge us, and it bugs me when someone compares apples and oranges and complains of the unfairness.&nbsp;&nbsp; None of us really wants to pay for symbols.&nbsp; Enchanters dont really want to pay for runes.&nbsp;&nbsp; Mages get fed up with taking packs of pearls to raids.&nbsp;&nbsp; Maybe there should be a way for all the component laiden classes to mitigate or remove the costs.&nbsp; Maybe there shouldnt.&nbsp;&nbsp; What we as a mass seem to _want_ is for it to be removed... Dont stop there however.&nbsp; If we deserve to have the costs removed for what we do special then so should everyone else for what they do special.<BR></P>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Laurri<br>(70 Cleric - Circle of Eternity - Veeshan)
							</div>
								
