<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=1957#M1957">67</a> of 113
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 359 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>The problem is that there IS no solution for the lvl 44-60 clerics.&nbsp; Now it's fine if you have a guild or a buddy to PL you from 44-65, but for casual players the mid to late 50's are as high as most go.&nbsp; If SOE is justified in putting a component cost on a spell that's combination hp/ac/symbol, then explain why there is no cost on combination hp/mana regen, or hp/str/dex.&nbsp; There is no justification, period.&nbsp; You want to argue that, "Well, we got the best HP buff, so we deserve to have to shell out 10p per cast" but that's nuts.&nbsp; And as far as trying to claim my money back for dots, one question..."Are you NUTS!"&nbsp; By standing up and demanding money up front for HP buff reagents I stand out amongst clerics and will quickly be marked as someone not to group with.&nbsp; Because of the reagent costs that only our class has to pay, we basically have to pay in plat for our xp time.&nbsp; Maybe X number of years ago people could get away with not casting symbols, but today it's "Temp me or beat it."&nbsp; And the days of FFA loot aren't over, almost no one I've grouped with ML's unless it's a raid or LDoN.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The fact remains that there are other spells out there just as sought after, sometimes moreso, than Temp/Aego/Virt.&nbsp; You may think Pot9 is a worthless spell, but for any caster or priest that is not looking to try their hand at tanking, Pot9 and symbol are the way to go, clerics included.&nbsp; HoS/Focus is HP, strength, AND Dexterity plus it stacks with Virtue.&nbsp; KEI/VoQ is something that every class except rogues, monks, warriors, and now berserkers, make sure they get before they go xping, and why not?&nbsp; Everyone thinks they NEED the mana regen these days.&nbsp; But do any of these spells even require a Cat's Eye Agate to cast?&nbsp; Why are we so special?&nbsp; I refuse to believe that cleric HP buffs are so extremely unbalanced that only a 10pp cost per cast can alleviate the pressure.&nbsp; Someone explain to me why clerics have to pay, 9 times out of 10 out of their own pocket, for a spell line that's no better, and I do stress no better, than KEI, Pot9, or Hos/Focus.&nbsp; Each of those buffs is equally needed, and suited to certain situations, and to claim that the Temp/Aego/Virtue spells are just so ungodly more powerful that we deserve to pay 10pp per cast is ludicrous.&nbsp; At your level it's an inconvenience, at mine it's the reason I can't afford my level 56 spells.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Damerr Flinn</DIV>
<DIV>55th Season Templar</DIV>
<DIV>Lanys T'Vyl</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
